[thinking] I'm considering the Kotlin standard library and its structure. It seems many stdlib-common functions are inline and might not be included in a JAR file. I'm realizing that the common JAR contains metadata and implementation classes. Is the kotlin-stdlib-common artifact actually just metadata-only? For the JVM, it looks like it includes common code as klib. But I think the JAR does include Kotlin metadata used by the compiler, though it may not have the runtime classes.
[thinking] 
